  "prompt": "What song plays over the end credits to the 2002 movie The Nest?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, specific details about the song that plays during the end credits of the 2002 movie **\"The Nest\"** are not widely documented in publicly available sources. This film is relatively obscure, and its soundtrack information isn't extensively listed on major databases like IMDb or popular music platforms.\n\nHere are a few steps you can take to identify the song:\n\n1. **Watch the End Credits Carefully:** Sometimes, the song title and artist are listed during the end credits themselves. Pausing or rewinding the credits can help you catch the information.\n\n2. **Check the IMDb Page:**\n   - Visit the [**IMDb page for \"The Nest\" (2002)**](https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0285293/).\n   - Look under the **\"Soundtrack\"** or **\"Music\"** sections, if available.\n\n3. **Look for a Soundtrack Listing:**\n   - Some films have official soundtrack releases. Searching for a soundtrack album associated with \"The Nest\" might provide the information you need.\n   \n4. **Explore Fan Forums and Communities:**\n   - Websites like [**Reddit**](https://www.reddit.com/) or [**Film Forums**](https://www.filmforums.com/) may have dedicated threads where fans discuss specific details about the movie, including its soundtrack.\n\n5. **Contact the Filmmakers or Production Company:**\n   - If possible, reaching out directly to the filmmakers or the production company may yield the information you're seeking.\n\n6. **Use Music Identification Apps:**\n   - If you have access to the movie, you can play the end credits song near a device with a music identification app like **Shazam** or **SoundHound**. These apps can often identify songs based on short audio clips.\n\nIf none of these methods yield the desired information, it might be that the song is part of the film's original score or composed specifically for the movie, making it less likely to be available as a standalone track.",
